CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `estuary-theatre`.testing.simple (

		flow_document STRING NOT NULL

		int INT64,
		str STRING NOT NULL,
		flow_document STRING NOT NULL

		id INT64 NOT NULL,
		array_int STRING,
		bool_field BOOL,
		float_field FLOAT64,
		flow_published_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
		multiple JSON,
		nested STRING,
		nullable_int INT64,
		str_field STRING NOT NULL,
		flow_document STRING NOT NULL

CLUSTER BY id;

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `estuary-theatre`.testing.formatted_strings (
		id INT64 NOT NULL,
		date DATE,
		datetime TIMESTAMP,
		flow_published_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
		int_and_str BIGNUMERIC(38,0),
		int_str BIGNUMERIC(38,0),
		num_and_str FLOAT64,
		num_str FLOAT64,
		time STRING,
		flow_document STRING NOT NULL
)
CLUSTER BY id;

estuary-theatre%2Ftesting%2Fduplicate_ke.Query:
MERGE INTO `estuary-theatre`.testing.duplicate_keys AS l
USING flow_temp_table_1 AS r
ON l.id = r.c0
WHEN MATCHED AND r.c4 IS NULL THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l.flow_published_at = r.c1, l.int = r.c2, l.str = r.c3, l.flow_document = r.c4
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
	INSERT (id, flow_published_at, int, str, flow_document)
	VALUES (r.c0, r.c1, r.c2, r.c3, r.c4);
